The total mortality rate, dM in equation (2), is the sum of a constant daily mortality rate that is meant to incorporate grazing, aging, and disease (d; Supplementary Table 1) and a term that accounts for breakage from waves (dw), such that12dM=d+Πdw.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
