The standard runs were spun up for 1 year, and the seeding was optimized by choosing the run initialization date that yielded the largest yearly biomass harvest (averaged across 2003–2019) for every grid point. Tropical and temperate brown seaweed runs were seeded with 50 g-DW m−2. Tropical and temperate red seaweed runs were seeded with 200 g-DW m−2 and 10 g-DW m−2, respectively, following examples in the literature (see Supplementary Tables 2–5). Seaweed are seeded with an initial nitrogen cell quota (Q0), such that15Q0=Qmin+N35Qmax−Qmin,\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
